<HEADLINE>Paisley MP ill</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>KEN SMITH</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830467</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PAISLEY MP Irene Adams is cutting short a holiday in America and
flying home after becoming ill in New York. It is believed she has been
suffering from heat stroke.Temperatures in New York have approached
100F.
Mrs Adams, who has been under considerable strain after publicly
standing up against the drug gangs in Paisley, is on holiday with her
daughter Barbara and son Allan.
The MP's assistant, Mr Bob Macaulay, said at her constituency office
in the town yesterday: ''She didn't feel well and went to hospital for a
check-up. Everything seems to be OK, but they are cutting short the
holiday.''
</TEXT>
