<TEXT>
KILMARNOCK MP Willie McKelvey, chairman of the all-party Scotch Whisky
Industry Parliamentary Group, yesterday visited United Distillers
packaging plant in the town to witness the first bottling of a premium
Scotch whisky, Johnnie Walker Gold Label.
The plant has recently undergone a #13m modernisation programme. The
young John Walker set up a shop in the town 175 years ago.
As a purveyor of wines and spirits, he began blending Scotch whiskies
to suit customers' individual needs and laid the foundations of the
global business empire which is now part of United Distillers.
