<HEADLINE>Hill sets fast lap</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>47</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830480</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DAMON Hill set the fastest lap yesterday, the final day of Formula One
testing at Silverstone, but his time of 1min 28.93sec was almost 0.8sec
slower than the best of the week -- by departing Williams team-mate
David Coulthard.
The Scot's future remained undecided after Williams announced that
they had signed Canadian Jacques Villeneuve to partner Hill next season.
Benetton, Ferrari -- who have signed world champion Michael Schumacher
in a two-year deal that could cost #32m -- and McLaren have been tipped.
But Coulthard's manager, Tim Wright, said: ''We're not in any hurry.
Coulthard's future is secure and he will be in a seat with a top-four
team.
''I am not saying it will necessarily be Ferrari, but I think a
Schumacher-Coulthard partnership is a dream team. If he is going to be
the greatest driver, he has to put himself up against the greatest.''
</TEXT>
