GRANITE CITY CLASSIC
LETHAM Grange professional David Scott won the #12,500 Granite City
Classic at Hazlehead yesterday. The 32-year-old former PGA Cup player
equalled the course record seven-under-par 63 set by Colin Gillies in
Wednesday's opening round to beat Glencorse's Colin Brooks by three
strokes.
Scott birdied the first three holes to move him into contention after
his opening 66. He reached the turn in 30 and four further birdies on
the back nine -- including the last where he rattled in an eight-footer
-- more than compensated for his bunker-induced bogey 5 at the 430-yard
fourteenth.
A double-bogey 6 at the 309-yard eighth blighted Brooks' chances.
