<TEXT>
* ROBERT Wiseman Dairies' #6.6m purchase of the Scottish milk
distribution business of the Co-operative Wholesale Society (CWS) has
been formally approved by the Government.
The Department of Trade and Industry said yesterday it would not refer
the deal, announced in June, to the Monopolies and Mergers Commission.
Robert Wiseman will acquire a CWS dairy in Glasgow and six milk
