<HEADLINE>Black rain</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830532</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MOSCOW: An asphalt and concrete plant in the central Russian region of
Mary-El has been ordered to close after it allowed 35 tonnes of boiling
tar to escape into the atmosphere, Itar-Tass news agency said. The tar
rose into the air before falling as black rain at temperature of 180
degrees Centigrade destroying a hectare of farmland.
</TEXT>
