<DOCID>GH950818-000079</DOCID>
<DATE>950818</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Crash kills three</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830544</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
COLOMBO: Two British women and the driver of their car were killed when
it collided with a bus on Sri Lanka. Andrea Smith, 34, died instantly
and Michelle Kerr, 32, died later in hospital. Both were from Yorkshire.
The driver, from Colombo, was also killed. Police have arrested the bus
driver.
