<DOCNO>GH950818-000080</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950818-000080</DOCID>
<DATE>950818</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Mandela is to divorce</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830545</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SOUTH AFRICA: President Nelson Mandela is to divorce his estranged
wife Winnie, four months after firing her from his Cabinet, reports said
yesterday. A South African radio station said lawyer Ismail Ayob
confirmed he had been retained by Mandela to arrange a settlement.
He said he has been told to open discussions with Winnie's lawyers and
to handle the issue ''sensitively''. Winnie's spokesman, Alan Reynolds,
said: ''They were hardly married. They had two years of marriage before
he went to prison and they were together a year before they separated.''
</TEXT>
