<HEADLINE>Over and out, and back again</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830584</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EDINBURGH Direct Aid had its CB and walkie-talkie radio equipment
stolen from its depot in Leith, then returned minutes before its latest
convoy set off on a mercy mission to wartorn Bosnia.
An off-duty policeman had spotted young children playing with what
appeared to be a toy walkie-talkie and alerted the local station when he
heard reports of the theft. The convoy will deliver four lorry-loads of
food, clothing, and toiletries to Sarajevo and Tuzla.
</TEXT>
