<HEADLINE>A true ideologue</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>976830598</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JOHN McKay writes on socialism with the enthusiasm of the true
ideologue. He says it has never been genuinely implemented. If it had
been, the world would be a better place (August 9).
So too would the world be a better place if Christianity (pick a
sect), Islam (likewise), Humanism, Buddhism, or just about any other
''ism'' was implemented at the expense of all others.
The trouble unfortunately is that human beings are too diverse in
nature and character to subscribe wholly to one perfect theory.
The alternative is to force people (for their own good, of course) to
embrace one's own version of the New Jerusalem, which is where people
with impeccable socialist credentials such as Benito Mussolini, Joseph
Goebbels, and Oswald Mosley step in.
And that's where I (among most others, I think) step out.
C Primrose,
107 Queen Margaret Drive,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
