<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830619</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A TEENAGER who interfered with the emergency lever of a train was
yesterday sentenced to 60 hours community service at Dumbarton Sheriff
Court. John Philips, 17, of Renton, Dunbartonshire, placed passengers
and crew in a state of fear and alarm on July 9 last year when he pulled
the emergency cord of the train three times as it stood at Renton
station, jamming one of the doors.
</TEXT>
