<TEXT>
It might look like the next-worst thing to the chain gang but people
are learning in the Cathkin Braes above Castlemilk that there's money in
old rock. Trainees Des Campbell, left, and Brian Harkins, both from
Castlemilk, are acquiring the time-honoured skills that can these days
bring in a good living as the older practitioners die out.
</TEXT>
