<DATE>950818</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Claim dismissed as rubbish</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976830636</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
INVERNESS residents were assured yesterday that it is OK to wash out
their wheelie bins with bleach. The district council was responding to a
claim made in leaflets by Highland Cleansing and Hygiene, which offered
its own wheelie-bin cleaning service at #18 a year.
The leaflet said: ''It is an offence to wash out bins into drains. The
maximum fine is #25,000.'' Denying this, the cleansing department
accused the firm of ''scaremongering''.
</TEXT>
